      "bookStockDetails": "Available",
      "aboutbook": "Tilo is a Mistress of Spices who has her shop Spice Bazaar located in Oakland. She helps people in solving their life's problems with the magic of the spices. All was going well until one friday evening an American walks into her shop(& life) and messes up everything she ever knew. In doing so she is forced to choose between her love for her spices or Raven( the American),A heart soothing reading which took me through the world of magic, traditional powers of spices, empathetic life stories and a beautiful love. It is relieving to know the sweetness of living a life of reality(Whatever challenges it might throw) than to run behind a world of fantasy which may or may not be true. ",
      "aboutAuthor": "Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni is the author of the Women's Prize-shortlisted The Mistress of Spices and other award-winning, bestselling books including Sister of My Heart and Arranged Marriage. Her books have been translated into 29 languages, and several of her works have been made into films and plays. Born in India, she lives in Houston with her husband and two sons.Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni is the award-winning author of 18 books. Her themes include the Indian experience, contemporary America, women, immigration, history, myth, and the joys and challenges of living in a multicultural world. Her work has been published in over 100 magazines and anthologies and translated into 29 languages, including Dutch, Hebrew, Hindi and Japanese. She has won numerous awards, including an American.Her latest novel is Oleander Girl (Simon and Schuster, 2013). Her upcoming novel is Before We Visit the Goddess (about 3 generations of women-- grandmother, mother and daughter-- who each examine the question what does it mean to be a successful woman. April 2016, Simon & Schuster.).She currently teaches in the nationally ranked Creative Writing program at the Univ. of Houston. She serves on the Advisory board of Maitri in the San Francisco Bay Area and Daya in Houston, organizations that help South Asian or South Asian American women in abusive situations. She is also closely involved with Pratham, an organization that helps educate children (especially those living in urban slums) in India.",
